    "contenu": "The document appears to be a recipe titled \"Summer Squash with Tomato and Cheddar in Chardonnay, Lemon Thyme Emulsion.\" Below is a structured breakdown of the recipe information and instructions found in the document:\n\n### Recipe Title\n**Summer Squash with Tomato and Cheddar in Chardonnay, Lemon Thyme Emulsion**\n\n### Introduction\nThe recipe provides a unique approach to handling zucchini by employing both cold and hot treatment to balance the taste experience. It is designed for serving four people and involves creating an emulsion as well as a vegetable stew. The dish showcases a mix of grilled zucchini, tomatoes, cheddar cheese, and a rich emulsion flavored with lemon thyme and Chardonnay. It is recommended for serving with grilled vegetables and seafood.\n\n### Serves\n**4**\n\n### Ingredients\n#### Emulsion\n- ½ cup dry white wine\n- 1 tablespoon sugar\n- Juice of ½ lemon\n- 1 teaspoon lemon thyme leaves (or ½ tablespoon regular thyme and 1 teaspoon julienned lemon zest)\n- 1 tablespoon extra virgin olive oil\n- Kosher salt\n\n#### Vegetable Stew\n- 4 round zucchinis or 2 small long zucchinis\n- 3 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil\n- 1 shallot, thinly sliced\n- 1 clove garlic, thinly sliced\n- 2 cups chopped, seeded tomato\n- Kosher salt\n- Freshly ground white pepper\n- 1 tablespoon polenta or fine cornmeal\n- 1/3 cup grated cheddar cheese\n\n### Instructions\n#### Emulsion Preparation\n1. Combine the white wine, sugar, lemon juice, and half of the thyme leaves in a medium saucepan.\n2. Heat over medium-high heat until fragrant but not yet simmering.\n3. Add the olive oil and use an emulsion blender (or whisk vigorously) to blend until smooth.\n4. Season with salt and keep warm over very low heat.\n\n#### Vegetable Stew Preparation\n1. Heat olive oil in a pan and sauté shallot and garlic.\n2. Add zucchini and cook until tender.\n3. Incorporate tomatoes, season with salt and white pepper.\n4. Stir in polenta or cornmeal to thicken.\n5. Once cooked, mix in grated cheddar cheese.\n\nThis structured format breaks down all components of the recipe, making it easy to follow and understand."
